Fulton Street, at, adjoining and west of the N.W. corner of Gold Street. Also shown is Gold Street, west side, north from Fulton, to and including Ann Streets.

About 1920.

Edwin Levick.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.

Fulton Street (foreground, diagonally from right to left) west from Gold Street (right lower corner) to William Street, as viewed north westward from No. 111 John Street. Shown is the 19 story Royal Insurance Co. Building and its 20 story adjunct under construction on the Gold Street frontage. Note to left the old Post Office dome and the overtowering Woolworth Building. In the far background is the North (Hudson) River and the Jersey Shore.

July 8, 1930.

P.L. Sperr
